From 1400 people questioned before the federal elections of 2010, the number of those who oppose Australia becoming a republic increased by 8 percent since 2008.
During her campaign for the 2010 federal election, Prime Minister Julia Gillard claimed that she believed Australia should become a republic by the end of Queen Elizabeth II's reign.
34 percent of those in the opinion poll share this view, hoping that Queen Elizabeth II would be the last Australian monarch.
At the extremes of the opinion poll, 29 percent of the respondents think that Australia should become a republic as soon as possible, while 31 percent believe that Australia should never become a republic.
