If you have seen the movie National Treasure, you might think that the treasure map was drawn on the back of the Declaration of Independence.
However, this is not true. Although there is a written note at the back of the document, it is not a treasure map.
On the reverse of the Declaration of Independence was the words: "Original Declaration of Independence dated July 4, 1776".
Although no one knows who wrote it, it is known that in the early days of its existence the large parchment document (its dimensions are 29¾ inches by 24½ inches) was rolled up for storage.
It was probably added as a label.
