The cave itself, which has been preserved over time, gives a clear image of Mohamed's spiritual inclinations.
Located at the top of one of the mountains north of Mecca, the cave is absolutely isolated from the rest of the world.
Actually it is not easily found, even if one knows it exists. When one is in the cave, that is total isolation.
Nothing else is visible except the bare, beautiful sky above and the many mountains around. Very little of this world is visible or audible from inside the cave.
The Great Pyramid in Giza is one of seven wonders that still stands today.
Built by the Egyptians in the third century B.C.E., the Great Pyramid is one of the largest pyramidal structures built to honor a deceased pharaoh.
The Giza plateau, or the "Giza Necropolis" in the Egyptian Valley of the Kings contains a few pyramids (among which the great pyramid is the largest), a few small tombs, a few temples and the Great Sphinx.
The great pyramid was built to honor the pharaoh Khufu, and among the smaller pyramids, tombs and temples many were built to honor the wives and relatives of Khufu.
The "arrow up" mark appears as V and the "arrow down" mark as a hook or a square without a lower side.
It means you have to start at the tip and push the bow, and down means you have to start at the heel (where your hand holds the bow) and draw the bow.
A bow up typically produces a more delicate sound, while the bow down is stronger and firmer.
Don't add your personal marks with a pen, but remember that the printed check marks are there for musical reasons, so they should usually be observed.
