Views of Aristotle were accepted on all subjects of science, including psychology.
As the knowledge of the Greeks declined, the West became divided from its Greek philosophical and scientific roots.
Many observed rhythms in physiology and behavior often critically depend on the presence of endogenous cycles and how the biological clock produces them.
Internal rhythms that do not simply respond to external periodic stimuli have been documented for most living organisms, including bacteria, fungi, plants, and animals.
Biological clocks are self-sufficient oscillators, which continue a period of repetitive self-functioning even without external stimuli.
The Hershey and Chase experiment was one of the leading assumptions that DNA is genetic material.
Hershey and Chase used bacteriophages, or viruses, to insert their DNA into a bacterium.
They performed two experiments, marking either the DNA of the bacteriophage with radioactive phosphorus or the protein of the bacteriophage with radioactive sulfur.
Mutations can have a spectrum of effects depending on the type of mutation, the importance of the involved piece of genetic material, and whether the involved cells are cells of the germ line.
Mutations in the cells of a germ line can pass to children, while mutations in other locations can cause cell death or cancer.
Nature-based tourism attracts people interested in visiting natural areas to enjoy the scenery, including flora and fauna.
Examples of local action include hunting, fishing, photography, birdwatching, and visiting parks and studying information about the ecosystem.
An example is to visit Borneo and there take photos and learn about orangutans.
Every morning people leave towns in their cars to go to their workplace, and are passed by others, whose goal is the place they just left.
In this dynamic non-motorized transport, everyone is somehow involved and contributing to a transport system based on the use of private cars.
Science now indicates that this massive carbon economy has transformed the biosphere from one of its stable states, which has supported human evolution over the past two million years.
Every person participates in society and uses transportation systems. Almost everyone complains about transportation systems.
In developed countries one rarely hears a similar level of complaints about the quality of water or the collapse of bridges.
Why transportation systems cause such complaints, why they fail every day? Are transportation engineers simply incompetent?
Traffic Flow is the study of the movement of individual drivers and vehicles between two points and the interactions that occur between them.
Unfortunately, studying traffic flow is difficult, as one cannot predict the behavior of the driver with a 100% certainty.
Good luck, drivers tend to behave within a sufficiently uniform arrangement; thus traffic flows strive to have some moderate uniformity and can be approximately presented mathematically.
To present traffic flow better, relationships were established among the three main characteristics: (1) flow, (2) density and (3) speed.
These relationships help plan, develop, and operate route facilities.
Insects were the first animals to fly. Their ability to fly helped them to evade enemies more easily and to find food and mates more effectively.
Most insects have the advantage of being able to fold their wings along the body.
This gives them a wider choice of small hiding places against predators.
Today the only insects that cannot fold their wings backwards are dragonflies and damselflies.
Thousands of years ago, a man named Aristarchus said that the Solar System moves around the Sun.
Some people thought he was right, but many believed the opposite: that the Solar System moves around the Earth, including the Sun (and even other stars).
It seemed prudent, because the Earth didn't feel like it was moving, did it?
The Amazon River is the second longest and the largest river on Earth. It carries more than 8 times more water than the second largest river.
The Amazon is also the widest river on Earth, sometimes six miles wide.
About 20 percent of the water that flows into the oceans from the planet's rivers comes from the Amazon.
The main river Amazon is 6387 km (3980 miles) long. It collects water from thousands of smaller rivers.
Although the construction of stone pyramids lasted until the end of the Old Empire, no one ever succeeded in surpassing the pyramids of Giza in size and the technical skill of their construction.
The Egyptians of the New Empire marvelled at the monuments of their predecessors, who had more than a thousand years before them.
The population of Vatican is around 800 people. It is the smallest independent state in the world and the state with the smallest population.
The Vatican City uses the Italian language in its laws and official relations.
The Italian is also the everyday language used by the majority of those who work in the state, while the Latin is often used in religious ceremonies.
All citizens of the Vatican City are Roman Catholics.
People knew about the basic chemical elements – such as gold, silver and copper – from ancient times, because these are found in nature in their basic form and are relatively easily extractable with primitive tools.
Philosopher Aristotle theorized that everything consists of a mixture of one or more of the four elements. It was about earth, water, air and fire.
This was more like the four states of matter (in the same order): solid, liquid, gaseous and plasma, although he further theorized that they become new substances to form what we see.
An alloy is essentially a mixture of two or more metals. Do not forget that in the periodic table there are many elements.
Elements like calcium and potassium are considered as metals. Yes, there are also metals like silver and gold.
You can also have alloys, in whose composition are small quantities of non-metallic elements such as carbon.
Everything in the Universe is made of matter. The entire matter consists of small particles called atoms.
Atoms are so incredibly small that trillions of them could fit into a point at the end of this sentence.
