Everyone who drives a vehicle into high latitudes or over mountain passes should be aware that there may be snow, ice, or frost.
On roads with ice or snow, friction is minimal and therefore one cannot drive as on bare asphalt.
During snowstorms, the snowfall capable of blocking you can fall very quickly.
Visibility can also be limited by falling snow or wind, by condensation, or by ice forming on the vehicle's windows.
On the other hand, snowy and icy weather is normal in many countries, but traffic flows mostly uninterrupted throughout the year.
