Pests can damage food, cause irritation or, worst of all, cause allergic reactions, spread toxins or transport infections.
Infectious diseases or dangerous animals capable of wounding or killing a person by force are generally not considered as calamities.
Duty-free shopping is the ability to buy goods exempt from taxes and duties in certain places.
Travelers to countries with high taxation can sometimes save a considerable amount of money, especially on products such as alcohol and tobacco.
The section between Point Marion and Fairmont presents the most challenging road conditions on the Buffalo-Pittsburgh highway, sometimes passing through isolated forest areas.
If you are not used to driving on country roads, be extremely careful: there are very steep inclines, narrow corridors and winding lanes.
Warning speed limits are remarkably lower than those of the preceding and following sections – often 35-40 mph (56-64 km/h) – and they are strictly enforceable, even more so otherwise.
It's noteworthy that cell phone service is much stronger here than in many other sections of the road, for example, in Pennsylvania Wilds.
German pastries are very tasty and in Bavaria they are very rich and diverse, similar to those of the neighboring country in the south, Austria.
There are many fruitful baked goods that contain apples throughout the year, and cherries and plums in the summer.
Many German baked goods also contain almonds, hazelnuts and other tree nuts. Popular cakes usually go very well with a cup of strong coffee.
If you want some small but rich doughnuts, taste those called Berliner, Pfannkuchen or Krapfen depending on the region.
A dish made of herbs and spices with meat or vegetables.
A substance can be either "dry" or "wet" depending on the amount of liquid.
Inland regions of northern India and Pakistan usually add yogurt to dishes; in southern India and some other coastal regions of the subcontinent, coconut oil is commonly used.
With 17,000 electable islands, Indonesian cuisine is a term that covers a wide range of regional cuisines across the country.
Used without additional qualifying words, the term generally refers to the cuisine originating from the central and eastern parts of the main island of Java.
Now widely available throughout the archipelago, Javanese cuisine offers various spicy dishes, with flavors preferred by Javanese people, that is chili peppers, chilies, sugar (especially Javanese coconut sugar) and various aromatic spices.
Hanging from both sides of the saddle, stirrups function as supports at the rider's feet.
They give the rider greater stability, but they can present security problems, as the rider's feet could potentially get caught in them.
If you fall off a horse and your foot is caught by a picket, you could be dragged by a running horse. To minimize this risk, various safety measures can be taken.
First, most riders wear riding boots with a high heel and a very narrow sole.
