Downhill winter sports, which include skiing and snowboarding, are popular sports in which one glides downhill on a snow-covered terrain having skis or a snowboard fixed to the feet.
Skiing is an important recreational activity with many enthusiasts, known as "ski bums" and who plan full vacations based on skiing at a specific location.
The idea of skiing is very old: cave paintings depicting skiers date back to 5000 BC.
Skiing has been calculated to have been a sport since at least the 17th century and in 1861 Norwegians founded the first pleasure skiing club in Australia.
Backcountry skiing: This activity is also known as ski touring, ski travel or ski migration.
It relates to alpine-style ski migration or mountain climbing, but it usually does not imply them, as these last ones occur on rugged terrain and require much stiffer skis and boots.
Think of the skiing route, as if it were a migratory route.
In good conditions you will be able to travel over distances a bit larger than during hiking, but you will only rarely reach the speeds of cycling without a heavy backpack on well-maintained roads.
Europe is a relatively small part of the world, but it has many independent countries. In normal circumstances, to travel through several countries one needs to fill out visas and go through passport controls again.
The awkward area however functions in this respect as if it were one single country.
Provided that one stays within that area, one can generally cross borders without the need to pass through passport control points.
Similarly, if you have a Schengen visa, you don't need to ask for a visa separately to each Schengen country, which saves you time, money and bureaucracy.
