Severe weather is the general term for any dangerous weather phenomenon capable of causing damage, a significant social disturbance, or loss of human life.
Severe weather can occur anywhere in the world and it consists of various types, which depend on the location, the terrain and atmospheric conditions.
Storms, hail, heavy precipitation, and forest fires are presentations and effects of severe weather, in addition to lightning storms, tornadoes, blizzards, and cyclones.
Regional and seasonal phenomena of severe weather include blizzards, snowstorms, winter storms, and sandstorms.
It is highly advisable that travelers be aware of any risk of severe weather that affects their area, as this can impact any travel plans.
