The capital of Moldova is Chisinau. The local language is Romanian, but Russian is widely used.
Moldova is a multi-ethnic republic that has suffered a small conflict.
In 1994, this conflict led to the creation of the self-declared Republic of Transnistria in the east of Moldova, which has its own government and currency, but is recognized by no member state of the UN.
Economic ties were resumed between these two parts of Moldova, although political negotiations failed.
The most important religion in Moldova is Orthodox Christianity.
