Christmas is one of the most important holidays of Christianity. It celebrates the birthday of Jesus.
Non-believers living in Christian countries or elsewhere in the whole world adopted many of the traditions of this festival.
Traditionally, one spends the Easter night sleepless in an outdoor location to see the sunrise.
It is obvious there are Christian theological explanations for this tradition, but it could be about a pre-Christian rite of spring and fertility.
On Easter Saturday night, more traditional churches often hold Easter vigil and the parishioners gather exactly at nightfall to celebrate the resurrection of Christ.
